The Comptroller of Nigeria Immigration Service (NIS) Command in Imo, Mr Okey Ezugwu has warned that any Immigration Officer found to be corrupt would be made to face the full wrath of the law. The Comptroller encouraged applicants to name unscrupulous officers who solicit bribes to hasten the passport application process. Ezugwu gave the directive while flagging off the 2022 Customer Service Week at the command’s headquarters in Owerri on Monday. Imo NIS Comptroller called on the public to demand their right to proper service delivery by officers of the command. Government belongs to you and it is run with your taxes; If they don’t let you see me it means they have something to hide, the comptroller said. According to the comptroller, “We are here to serve you and we want to ensure that you are satisfied with the services we provide; to enable us achieve this, we solicit your opinions, complaints and suggestions The comptroller also commissioned shelters designed to accommodate applicants adding that they were constructed to ensure people are comfortable while waiting. While performing the ceremony, the comptroller urged applicants to present their complaints, opinions and suggestions to his office, assuring that all complaints would be addressed speedily. He said the NIS is committed to ensuring that applicants are treated with courtesy and that all applications follow due process to discourage racketeering and delays. “We have put up these structures to make applicants comfortable while they wait for their applications to be processed to demonstrate our commitment to improved service delivery.”